{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846802602,"sessionID":"ses_2874b3e7cffeHcaG0cXjiTR7WF","part":{"id":"prt_d78b4cc55001AYUbcgnnEwVpbJ","messageID":"msg_d78b4c275001qNp8bH4FRe7SRu","sessionID":"ses_2874b3e7cffeHcaG0cXjiTR7WF","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_5254398ba57e414ebcfa8258","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project structure thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project layout and directory structure\n2. What's in the pkg/agentd module specifically\n3. Any existing tasks.md files or similar checklists in the project\n4. Any design documents related to \"AR-018\" or \"空闲清理控制器\" (idle cleanup controller)\n5. Look for Stage ST-3 related documents or completion markers\n6. Any existing patterns for how tasks are structured in this project\n\nSearch for files matching patterns like:\n- **/tasks.md\n- **/AR-018*\n- **/*idle*cleanup*\n- **/*st-3*\n- **/ST-3*\n- pkg/agentd/**\n\nAlso read key files in pkg/agentd to understand the current state of the module.\n\nReturn all findings including file paths, relevant content summaries, and any patterns you discover about how this project structures work.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2874b200cffexpWsJJgUBIr1IP (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the agentcube project. Here is my complete report:\n\n---\n\n## AgentCube Project Structure -- Complete Analysis\n\n### 1. Overall Project Layout and Directory Structure\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\n├── .sdd_prompt.md           -- SDD (Spec-Driven Development) prompt template for AR-018\n├── changes/                  -- All change requests (AR-001 through AR-018)\n│   ├── AR-001/ ... AR-018/   -- Each contains: proposal.md, design.md, delta-spec.md, tasks.md\n├── ci-cd/\n├── cli-toolkit/\n├── client-go/                -- Generated Kubernetes client code\n├── cmd/\n│   └── picod/                -- PicoD binary entry point (cmd/picod/main.go)\n│   └── [agentd/]             -- NOT YET CREATED (planned for AR-018)\n├── code-execution/\n├── coverage.out\n├── delta-spec.md\n├── deployment/\n├── design.md                 -- AR-016 design document (PicoD File Management API)\n├── go.mod                    -- Module: github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube, Go 1.25.0\n├── go.sum\n├── idle-cleanup/\n│   ├── design.md             -- Idle cleanup design spec\n│   └── spec.md               -- Idle cleanup requirements spec\n├── integrations/\n├── pkg/\n│   ├── apis/runtime/         -- CRD type definitions\n│   ├── common/types/         -- Shared types\n│   ├── picod/                -- PicoD in-sandbox daemon (13 files)\n│   ├── router/               -- HTTP router/proxy (16 files)\n│   ├── store/                -- Redis/Valkey session store (9 files)\n│   └── workloadmanager/      -- Workload manager (4 subdirs: handler/, middleware/, reconciler/, response/)\n├── project.md                -- Project context document\n├── proposal.md               -- AR-011 proposal (Router JWT Auth)\n├── python-sdk/\n├── sandbox-orchestration/\n│   └── design.md             -- Sandbox orchestration design\n├── session-routing/\n│   └── design.md             -- Session routing design\n├── session-store/\n├── test_spec.md\n└── testing/\n```\n\n**Key architectural components** (from project.md):\n- **Router** (Deployment :8080) -- HTTP proxy with session-aware routing\n- **WorkloadManager** (Service :8080) -- K8s CRD controller for sandbox lifecycle\n- **Agentd** (planned) -- Idle cleanup controller (AR-018)\n- **PicoD** -- In-sandbox daemon for file/execution operations\n- **Session Store** -- Redis/Valkey backed\n\n---\n\n### 2. The `pkg/agentd` Module -- Current State\n\n**`pkg/agentd/` does NOT yet exist.** Neither does `cmd/agentd/`. These are the deliverables of AR-018.\n\nThe planned structure (from AR-018 design.md) is:\n```\ncmd/agentd/\n└── main.go              -- Binary entry: Scheme registration, Manager construction, start\npkg/agentd/\n├── reconciler.go        -- Reconciler struct + Reconcile + SetupWithManager\n├── reconciler_test.go   -- Unit tests (fake client)\n└── const.go             -- SessionExpirationTimeout constant\n```\n\n**Key dependency note:** AR-018 requires a new constant `LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"` to be defined in `pkg/workloadmanager/const.go` (a new file). Currently, this key exists in two places with different values:\n- `pkg/router/config.go`: `\"agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity\"` (used by Router)\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/constants.go`: No `LastActivityAnnotationKey` defined (only `AnnotationIdleTimeout = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"`)\n\nThe AR-018 design specifies the value should be `\"last-activity-time\"` and should live in `pkg/workloadmanager/const.go`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Existing tasks.md Files and Checklists\n\n**18 tasks.md files found**, one per AR:\n\n| File | Module | Size | Stage |\n|------|--------|------|-------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-001/tasks.md` | pkg/apis | S | ST-4 (Implementation) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-002/tasks.md` | -- | -- | ST-3 (Design Complete) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-004/tasks.md` | -- | -- | ST-3 (Design Complete) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-005/tasks.md` | -- | -- | ST-3 (Design Complete) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-006/tasks.md` | -- | -- | ST-3 (Design Complete) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md` | -- | -- | ST-3 (Design Complete) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md` | -- | -- | ST-3 (Design Complete) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md` | -- | -- | ST-3 (Design Complete) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md` | -- | -- | ST-3 (Design Complete) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-012/tasks.md` | -- | -- | ST-3 (Design Complete) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-013/tasks.md` | -- | -- | ST-3 (Design Complete) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md` | -- | -- | ST-3 (Design Complete) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-015/tasks.md` | -- | -- | ST-3 (Design Complete) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-016/tasks.md` | pkg/picod | M | ST-3 (Design Complete) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md` | pkg/picod | S | ST-3 (Design Complete) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md` | pkg/agentd | S | ST-3 (Design) completed |\n\n---\n\n### 4. Design Documents Related to AR-018 / Idle Cleanup Controller\n\n**AR-018 documents** (all in `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-018/`):\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `proposal.md` (247 lines) | Purpose, scope, architecture, impact analysis, alternatives, acceptance criteria |\n| `design.md` (569 lines) | Full technical design: architecture, data structures, API contracts, core implementation code, testing strategy, deployment manifests |\n| `delta-spec.md` (352 lines) | Formal requirements with Gherkin-style scenarios |\n| `tasks.md` (32 lines) | Task checklist (currently a stub with single T1 placeholder) |\n\n**Idle-cleanup reference documents** (in `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/idle-cleanup/`):\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `design.md` (126 lines) | Package-level design for `pkg/agentd`: Reconciler algorithm, SetupWithManager, binary entry point |\n| `spec.md` (69 lines) | Requirements spec with Given/When/Then scenarios |\n\n**Key design points for AR-018:**\n- **Reconciler** watches `Sandbox` CR (`agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`)\n- Reads `last-activity-time` annotation from Sandbox metadata\n- `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n- Expired sandboxes are deleted; not-yet-expired ones requeue with `RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)`\n- Manager disables metrics (`BindAddress: \"0\"`) and health probe (`HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\"`)\n- Delete is idempotent (`IsNotFound` treated as success)\n\n---\n\n### 5. Stage ST-3 Related Documents and Completion Markers\n\n**Stage convention** found in tasks.md headers:\n- Older ARs (AR-002 through AR-012): `> **Stage**: ST-3 (Design Complete)`\n- Newer ARs (AR-013 through AR-018): `> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed`\n\n**All 18 ARs have reached ST-3 (Design Complete).** The AR-018 tasks.md explicitly states:\n```\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n```\n\nThis means the design phase is done and AR-018 is ready for **ST-4 (Implementation)**.\n\nThe `.sdd_prompt.md` file confirms: `[Stage ST-1 completed]` (referring to an earlier stage in the SDD workflow).\n\n---\n\n### 6. Task Structure Patterns in This Project\n\nThe project follows a consistent **Spec-Driven Development (SDD)** pattern. Each AR has 4 standard documents:\n\n```\nchanges/AR-NNN/\n├── proposal.md     -- Why, what, scope, alternatives, acceptance criteria\n├── design.md       -- Architecture, data structures, API contracts, implementation details, testing strategy\n├── delta-spec.md   -- Formal requirements with Gherkin scenarios (SHALL/MUST language)\n└── tasks.md        -- Actionable task checklist for implementation\n```\n\n**tasks.md structure pattern** (from AR-017 and AR-016 as exemplars):\n\n```markdown\n# AR-NNN -- Title -- Tasks\n\n> **Module:** pkg/xxx\n> **Language:** Go\n> **Size:** S/M/L\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-NNN/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-NNN/design.md`, `changes/AR-NNN/delta-spec.md`\n\n## T1. Task Title\n- [ ] 1.1 Sub-task description\n- [ ] 1.2 Sub-task description\n**Verification:** How to verify\n\n---\n\n## T2. Task Title\n...\n\n## Task Dependencies\n```\nT1\n│\nT2 ── T3 ── T4\n      │     │\n      T5    T6\n      │     │\n      └─────┴── T7\n```\n\n**Parallel execution:** Notes on which tasks can run in parallel\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n| # | Criterion | Command |\n|---|-----------|---------|\n| AC1 | 编译通过 | `go build ./pkg/xxx/...` |\n| AC2 | 全部测试通过 | `go test ./pkg/xxx/... -v -count=1` |\n| AC3 | 无竞态条件 | `go test -race ./pkg/xxx/...` |\n| AC4 | 无 lint 警告 | `go vet ./pkg/xxx/...` |\n```\n\n**Key patterns observed:**\n1. Tasks are numbered T1, T2, ... with sub-tasks 1.1, 1.2, ...\n2. Each task ends with a **Verification** section describing how to confirm completion\n3. A **Task Dependencies** ASCII diagram shows execution order and parallelism opportunities\n4. **Acceptance Criteria** table maps criteria to specific verification commands\n5. Common gate commands: `go build`, `go test -v -count=1`, `go test -race`, `go vet`, `go mod tidy`\n6. AR-018's tasks.md is currently a **stub** -- only has a single `T1. TODO` with `- [ ] 1.1` placeholder\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key Findings for AR-018 Implementation\n\n1. **`pkg/agentd/` does not exist yet** -- needs to be created with `const.go`, `reconciler.go`, `reconciler_test.go`\n2. **`cmd/agentd/` does not exist yet** -- needs `main.go`\n3. **`pkg/workloadmanager/const.go` does not exist yet** -- needs `LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"`\n4. **AR-018 tasks.md is a stub** -- needs to be fleshed out following the pattern from AR-016/AR-017\n5. **Design is complete** (ST-3 done) -- all specs are ready for implementation\n6. **There is a potential annotation key conflict**: Router uses `\"agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity\"` while AR-018 design specifies `\"last-activity-time\"` -- this discrepancy should be resolved\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2874b200cffexpWsJJgUBIr1IP","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775846612977,"end":1775846802599}}}}
